libversion
------------------------------------------
Advanced version string comparison library.

Need to compare software, package or whatever versions? Comparing 1.0 and 1.1
could be easy, but are you ready for more complex cases like 1.2-x.3~alpha4?
libversion is, which is proven by using the library in Repology project which
relies on comparing software version strings, even if they are written in
different formats.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-2.9.0-3
  libversion-devel-2.2.0-1bl1
  libversion0-2.2.0-1bl1
  pkg-config-0.29.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.29-1
  cmake-3.6.2-1
  cygport-0.24.1-1
  gcc-core-6.4.0-1
  make-4.2.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/repology/libversion

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/repology/libversion/archive/2.2.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libversion-2.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libversion-2.2.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libversion-2.2.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libversion-2.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libversion0-2.2.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libversion-devel-2.2.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libversion)
  /usr/bin/version_compare.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libversion.README
  /usr/share/doc/libversion/ALGORITHM.md
  /usr/share/doc/libversion/CHANGES.md
  /usr/share/doc/libversion/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libversion/README.md
  /usr/share/doc/libversion/TODO.md

(libversion0)
  /usr/bin/cygversion-0.dll

(libversion-devel)
  /usr/include/libversion/version.h
  /usr/lib/libversion.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libversion.pc

